\subsection{Complex Numbers}

By our normal means of dealing with numbers, $x^2 = -1$ will always be incomputable. However, Complex Numbers offer us a means of representing $x^2 = -1$ as a computable statement. This is done by adding a second dimension to the humble number line, where numbers can now be represented with a \textbf{real} component, and an \textbf{imaginary} component.

